</md></sn><sn><md>### Running Python Commands as a String

Python code can be executed directly from the command line using the `-c` option:

```bash
python -c 'print("Hello, World")'
```

##### Output

```text
Hello, World
```

This is especially useful when combining scripts or automating tasks in shell environments.
</md></sn><sn><md>### Package Management

The recommended package manager for Python is **pip**. To install a package:

```bash
pip install numpy
```

On Windows, if pip is not in PATH:

```bash
python -m pip install numpy
```
